Within surge band so did not apply SRC. Suspect I applied the SRC yesterday before the orifice has stabilized post purge, explaining the positive SRC today post purge. Stage corrections will be difficult and require some drifts to account for silting of orifice and consider adjusting the 06-21 SRC based on it being reset prior to stabilizing. column13: Large log jam d/s from gauge.
column14: Conventional from bridge ~500-750m d/s of gauge. Lots of debris floating down requiring lots of cleaning of price meter. Had issues with pentacount contact around the 6th panel and took a long time to fix. Mmmnt mean time likely biased early since majority of flow was measured after we fixed it. Trees floating down required some shots to be ended before 40s. My sounding may have been biased deep from velocities pulling weight and line back, but did my best to err on the side of shallower. MGH calc in field review. Used my estimated -0.066m SRC, adjust as you see fit. Used a mix of 1, 0.99 and 0.98 for angles. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (IVE Value). @ Took WL at arrival and found -0.058 SRC. Purged to clear any silt and found we took WL from ~8m upstream of orifice.  Took another WL as close as possible to orifice and found -0.026m SRC. Applied SRC as quickly as possible, ended up being just after 12:45 reading.  WL seems to drop ~0.003-0.005m between every logged value so silting was likely causing around 0.040m of the initial found SRC. WL rapidly dropping during visit so accepting 2.867 logger post reset vs 2.875 DWL Operating tech to validate but for the interim possibly a -0.066 shift until after 12:35 reading, then a -0.026 until 12:50. Mid-section

Good ADCP mmnt from bridge just above massive log jam.  Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of -0.045 and Gage Correction of 0.000 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 2.582 Larger SRC than i would like. Most likely orifice is silted from high water event. Purged orifice block but did not sound silted and seemed to recover somewhat. Purged again @ 11:40 and reset sensor. Had to leave station with around a 20 mm band of silted data since i cant get to pipe to pull orifice up. May clear out as the stage drops as this site tends to do.  Cant get to orifice block to kick out at this stage. Too deep. ADCP by Moving Boat ADCP MMNT HAD A DIRECTIONAL BIAS ON IT WITH MORE WATER MEASURED LEFT TO RIGHT AND LESS WATER RIGHT TO LEFT. I'M NOT SURE IF THIS IS COMMON AT HIGHER FLOWS OR IF IT HAD TO DO WITH MOVING BED OR EVEN THE MASSIVE LOG JAM DIRECTLY BELOW THE MMNT SECTION TN.  Dec 2021:  USED GGA. REMOVED A FEW TRANSECTS BECAUSE OF GPS ERRORS. STILL 797seconds of data (>720s) edges <5% of flow. good pitch and roll.  good compass cal.    The Directional Bias is likely caused from local magnetic interference, and cant really be helped. I adjusted the mag'n declination to 6degrees in QRev. this removes the directional bias and makes COV 1.25%, but the final Q is 95.9cms (rather than 94.7cms used). BT with 6.6% MB applied is 92.7cms. all within 3% of each other.    good mmnt considering conditions.  MDF
